titles.short: A Dino-Mite Lunch/Baby Hugo
titles.full: A Dino-Mite Lunch/Baby Hugo

summaries.short: Esme and Roy teach Tillie the importance of taking a lunch break and show Hugo the benefits of being a big kid.
summaries.full: It’s lunchtime, but hungry Tillie’s too busy playing dino-racecars to eat! How will Esme and Roy convince her to take a break to refuel? Later, when big kid Hugo decides he’d rather be a baby again, the Monster Sitters host a game-show to prove that being a big kid is loads of fun, too.

summaries.short: The Monster Sitters help Snugs learn patience and show Simon the beauty in his artwork, even if it’s not perfect.
summaries.full: Snugs doesn’t want to wait for “later,” he wants to eat his cupcakes now! Can Esme and Roy help the cute little monster learn patience? Next, the Monster Sitters show aspiring artist Simon that each of his imperfect paintings is special.

titles.short: Party Time/The Really Really Big Race
titles.full: Party Time/The Really Really Big Race

summaries.short: Esme and Roy's plans to throw a party go awry. Simon comes to Tillie's house for a big race.
summaries.full: Esme and Roy find out that five little monsters are coming over, so they decide to throw a party. But things don't go according to plan. Simon comes to Tillie's house for a big race, but soon discovers that he doesn't like racing. Esme and Roy need to find a way for them to play.
